GoNext License — DRAFT / PLACEHOLDER
=====================================

This LICENSE file is a placeholder while the licensing decision is finalized.

Current direction (subject to confirmation):

  • Core (Go API, admin app, public app, workers, importers):
    Business Source License 1.1 (BSL 1.1) OR Functional Source License 1.1
    (FSL 1.1), with conversion to Apache License 2.0 after a defined period
    (currently leaning toward 2 years for FSL 1.1, or 4 years per-file for
    BSL 1.1).

  • Plugin SDK and theme SDK (everything under packages/ts/sdk and
    packages/go/sdk once they exist):
    Apache License 2.0 from day one. No restrictions on plugin or theme
    authors.

  • First-party reference plugins and themes (everything under plugins/
    and themes/):
    Same license as core (BSL 1.1 / FSL 1.1 with auto-conversion).

  • Documentation, design docs, ADRs, proposals (everything under docs/
    and adr/):
    Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC-BY-4.0).

Rationale for source-available core: this project intends to be financially
sustainable for its maintainer (Singleton-Solution) via hosted SaaS,
commercial licensing, and premium first-party plugins. A purely permissive
license (Apache / MIT) on core would allow hyperscalers to host GoNext as a
managed service in direct competition with the maintainer, which would
undermine the funding model that pays for the project's continued
development. Source-available licenses with delayed open-source conversion
(BSL, FSL) are the standard solution adopted by HashiCorp Terraform, Sentry,
CockroachDB, MariaDB MaxScale, Couchbase Server, and others.

Rationale for permissive plugin SDK: plugin authors will not invest in
building on GoNext if the SDK they import is encumbered. Apache 2.0 on the
SDK signals that plugin code is the author's to license as they choose.

All contributors will be required to sign a Contributor License Agreement
(CLA) granting Singleton-Solution the right to relicense their contributions.
This is required to maintain the licensing flexibility above; see
adr/0002-cla.md once it is committed.

The licensing decision will be finalized before the project accepts external
code contributions. Until then, treat this software as "source available, all
rights reserved by Singleton-Solution" — you may read it, fork it, and
contribute back, but commercial use, redistribution, and modification rights
are not yet granted.

For the rationale and full discussion, see:
  - docs/proposals/14-proposals-strategic.md, proposal S2
  - adr/0001-licensing.md (when committed)

Copyright (c) 2026 Singleton-Solution. All rights reserved (pending final
license selection).

Questions: open a discussion at
https://github.com/Singleton-Solution/GoNext/discussions
